        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 6:10PM PDT by NWS Spokane WA</headline>
        <description>At 610 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Priest River, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of western Bonner
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
